where I want to be.

789
00:43:50,064 --> 00:43:51,598
I don't care what you want, and
I don't care what they want.

790
00:43:51,632 --> 00:43:53,533
It's over.
Let's go.

791
00:43:53,568 --> 00:43:56,070
I don't know why I assumed
you were more open-minded.

792
00:43:56,104 --> 00:43:58,973
Well, I'm not. I
understand the temptation,

793
00:43:59,007 --> 00:44:00,941
and I know everyone your
age is running away

794
00:44:00,976 --> 00:44:03,611
and screwing around, but you can't.
You're a mother.

795
00:44:03,645 --> 00:44:06,948
— Ellery has everything he needs.
— He needs his mother.

796
00:44:06,982 --> 00:44:09,251
I'm sorry, but you
don't get to do this!

797
00:44:09,284 --> 00:44:11,352
Goodbye, Daddy.

798
00:44:13,989 --> 00:44:16,858
Let me go!
Let me go right now!

